# Agent coding guidelines (template)

Read together with **`docs/PROJECT.md`** when that file exists (project-specific Level 2).

## Docs sync

When you add or change a **script**, **session field**, **hook behavior**, or **workflow step**, update in the **same change**:

- [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) — agent entry behavior
- [SESSIONS.md](../../SESSIONS.md) — commands or lifecycle
- Relevant `.cursor/skills/*/SKILL.md` or `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` — skill or rule behavior
- [docs/REPOS.md](../../docs/REPOS.md) — registry or worktree semantics

Do not duplicate: link to the canonical doc; one source of truth per concept.

## Test minimum

- **Python** under `scripts/lib/` → unit test in matching `scripts/test_*.py`
- **Shell** under `scripts/` → smoke test or exercised path in existing test suite
- **Session binding / guard** logic → happy path + one failure or edge case in `scripts/test_session_binding.py`
- **Product worktree** changes → follow [docs/PROJECT.md](../../docs/PROJECT.md) when present

## Level 2 (project)

Copy [docs/PROJECT.md.example](../../docs/PROJECT.md.example) to `docs/PROJECT.md` and fill stack, doc map, and test commands for your product repos.
